    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-07-09T10:02:40+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-09T10:02:40+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-09T00:32:40Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-09T00:32:40Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system centred near Tasmania extends a ridge over SA. A weak trough over northern SA will move slowly eastwards throughout today. A cold front will move across the south during Saturday followed by another front near southern coasts on Sunday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW014" description="North East Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-07-09T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-10T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-08T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-09T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Medium chance of showers north of Leigh Creek, slight chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm north of Leigh Creek in the late morning and afternoon. Winds east to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending south to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h in the middle of the day then becoming light in the late evening. Daytime maximum temperatures between 15 and 19.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 10:50am to 1:50pm, UV Index predicted to reach 3 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-07-10T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-11T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-09T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-10T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog. Slight chance of a shower east of Leigh Creek, near zero chance elsewhere. Light winds. Overnight temperatures falling to between 6 and 10 with daytime temperatures reaching between 16 and 19.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-07-11T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-12T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-10T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-11T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. The chance of morning fog east of Leigh Creek. Medium chance of showers east of Leigh Creek, near zero chance elsewhere. Light winds becoming west to northwesterly 20 to 30 km/h during the morning then tending west to southwesterly during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to around 8 with daytime temperatures reaching between 18 and 21.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-07-12T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-13T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-11T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-12T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Winds south to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 5 and 9 with daytime temperatures reaching between 15 and 19.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
